def: A short piece of pipe having a lateral outlet, used to connecta line of pipe with a pipe at a right angle with the line; -- socalled because it resembles the letter T in shape.
To make eternal. [Obs.]Fame . . . eternifies the name. Mir. for Mag.
To grasp with or hold in the hand. [R.] J. Barlow.
The employment, arts, or practices of a pander. Bp. Hall.
Formerly, the chief magistrate of the United Provinces ofHolland; also, the governor or lieutenant governor of a province.
A suborder of copepod Crustacea, including a large number ofremarkable forms, mostly parasitic on fishes. The young, however, areactive and swim freely. See Illustration in Appendix.
The breastplate of a horse's armor or harness. [Spelt alsopeitrel.] See Poitrel. [Obs.] Chaucer.
An agreement or understanding between the chief Europeanpowers, the United States, and Japan in 1900 to take only jointaction in the Chinese aspect of the Eastern Question.
Groats; coarse flour or meal. [Obs.] Sir. H. Wotton.

The fluid which is excreted from the skin of an animal; thefluid secreted by the sudoriferous glands; a transparent, colorless,acid liquid with a peculiar odor, containing some fatty acids andmineral matter; perspiration. See Perspiration.In the sweat of thy face shalt thou eat bread. Gen. iii. 19.
